{
  "id": "019d05af-1692-72e1-adfa-fbe3ec39ece1",
  "content": "# RAG Abstraction — Config-Driven Component Selection (2026-03-19)\n\nImplemented config-driven retriever and augmenter selection in the RAG pipeline.\n\n## What Changed\n- Added `retriever` and `augmenter` string fields to RagConfig\n- Factory pattern in create_rag_pipeline() selects by config name\n- Graceful fallback: graph_expand → vector if no graph store\n- Backward compatible: existing configs default to graph_expand + structured\n\n## Config\n```toml\n[rag]\nretriever = \"graph_expand\"  # or \"vector\"\naugmenter = \"structured\"\n```\n\n## Future Phases\n- Phase 2: Add hybrid (BM25+vector), reranker, temporal retrievers\n- Phase 3: External retriever plugins via JSONL IPC (like adapter system)\n\n## Design\nFull plan at docs/plans/2026-03-19-rag-abstraction-plan.md",
